title: For Trade:  Rare S&W 686 3" CS-1 2M 357 Magnum - U.S. Customs
location: Fort Mill & Matthews - Albemarle & Columbia, Charlotte, North Carolina
postcontent: Up for trade is a rare S&W model 686 3" that was made for the U.S. Customs back in the mid 1980's. If you don't know what a CS-1 2M is, just Google it. Tons of information on the Smith & Wesson Forum. It's believed that fewer than 1400 of the 3" carried by plainclothes Customs officers exist today. When Clinton came into office, Janet Reno switched to semi-autos and canceled the civilian trade-in program. Some made it into the hands of various gun dealers but the rest were ordered destroyed. These are the finest 686's ever made. Even by todays Performance Center standards. All stainless with a bead blast finish and Pachmayr grips. Also included is the finger groove black pepper grips and the holster that came with it when I bought it 3 years ago. Not sure if the holster was what the agent carried it in but it's obviously been with the firearm for a long time. It's also a S&W stamped holster. The firearm is mechanically perfect (locks up tight!) showing only honest wear from carry and use. The trigger is amazing. Single action is maybe 2 oz and the double action is similar to a two stage match rifle trigger. No guessing when it goes bang! Breaks like a glass rod exactly when you want it to. When you research it, you'll understand why it's so unique and the tolerance tests it had to endure to be accepted for duty. Now, I'm trading this simply because I don't use it. The last time I had it at the range was maybe two years ago. Since then I've become more of a bench rest shooter. Mainly interested in high power, long range, big bore rifles. 338 Lapua, 338 RUM, 30 WSM, etc. Would also be interested in high powered handguns. Magnum Research BFR in 45-70, S&W 460 or possible Freedom Arms 454 Casull. Coonan Arms 357 Magnum 1911 or other full size, high quality 1911's in 45 ACP. I've been considering this for some time and my only hesitation with listing it was I don't really know what I want. I'm obviously in no hurry to trade so you may see this one on here for 2 weeks, 2 months or even 2 years! If this listing is up, the firearm is still available. I'll respond quickly to serious offers and/or offers I'm interested in. Low end items or silly responses will not be acknowledged. Would like to stay local but will possibly travel for the right trade. More pictures available. Thanks for your interest!

title: For Sale:  Sig Saur M400 Enhanced AR15 with Trijicon TA11F ACOG and SureFire M952V Weapons Light
postcontent:
Selling my like new Sig Saur M400 Enhanced AR15 with a Trijicon TA11F ACOG and Surefire M952V LED Weapons Light.  $2,900 OBO.  Would possibly sell rifle only if interested. $1000. Other than that, it sells as a combo. Would also possibly trade for  Yamaha Yfz450r

Rifle Description:
THE SIGM400 SERIES ENHANCED RIFLE, is designed for use in law enforcement, military operations, the sporting field, as well as competitive shooting. The SIGM400 is a true AR platform tactical rifle with unparalleled accuracy. A 16” Nitride treated barrel provides superior corrosion resistance, and a 7075-T6 aircraft grade aluminum forged lower receiver adds to the durability and reliability that users come to expect from SIG SAUER. This ODG version with Black upper and lower receiver, OD Green polymer Magpul MOE forend, grip and collapsible stock.

Trijicon Description:
Trijicon TA11F ACOG 3.5x35 Scope with Chevron BAC Reticle includes Trijicon Flat Top Adapter TA51. The ranging reticle of the Trijicon Gunsight isimage calibrated for 5.56mm (.223 cal) flat-top rifles out to 800 meters. The chevron reticle is designed to be zeroed using the tip at 100 meters. The width of the chevron at the base is 5.53 MOA which is 19" at 300 meters. This allows range estimation for silhouette targets. Trijicon TA11F-A 3.5 x 35mm ACOG Advanced Combat Optical Gunsights hit fast in any light. Trijicon ACOG 3.5 x 35 Riflescopes are internally-adjustable, compact telescopic sights with tritium illuminated reticle patterns for use in low light or at night. Bindon Aiming Concept (BAC) models feature bright daytime reticles using fiber optics which collect ambient light. Trijicon 3.5x35 ACOGs combine traditional, precise distance marksmanship with close-in aiming speed. Although Trijicon ACOG 3.5 x 35 Rifle Scopes TA-11F have many features which are very advantageous for military use, they were developed by Trijicon without government funding. Designed for use with the M16 family, every feature of its mechanical and optical design was chosen for a single purpose: to provide increased hit potential in all lighting conditions - without failure-prone batteries.

 Surefire M925V LED light Description:
The M952V Millennium® Universal WeaponLight attaches by means of an integral Swing-Lever™ rail clamp to long guns equipped with a Picatinny rail. It utilizes one sealed LED unit to produce both brilliant white light and invisible infrared radiation for use with night vision devices. The white beam is configured for close- to medium-range applications. Changing back and forth from white output to infrared output is accomplished by a push/twist action on the M952V head, which self-locks into the selected output mode. The tailcap switch assembly features a momentary/constant-on pushbutton switch and a momentary-on tape switch (7-inch cable) that attaches to your preferred location via self-stick Velcro® backing. Available in Black (BK) or Desert Tan (TN) body color.

title: For Trade:  Rare S&W 53 22 Rem Jet 8 3/8 Excellent+ with Extras
location: Matthews Fort Mill Albemarle Columbia, Charlotte, North Carolina
postcontent:
Up for trade is a rare Smith & Wesson model 53 chambered in 22 Center-fire Magnum. A collaboration between Remington and S&W back in the 1960's. 4", 6" and the 8 3/8". Was designed as a small game hunting and target grade revolver. Wildcats were all the rage back then! It failed to catch on due to the cases backing out if they had oil on them or in the chambers. I always swab the chambers with rubbing alcohol before a range session and I've never had one to back out. Even after shooting 24+ rounds in a row. I bought this from a collector in N. Augusta about 6 years ago. As much as I enjoy collecting, I prefer to shoot. If I own it, it won't sit in a safe. I really don't shoot this one often. Maybe it needs to go to someone who'll enjoy it more than me. As stated in another listing of mine, I'm getting away from hand-gunning in favor of bench rest. Anyway, this one is in outstanding original condition. Pictures don't come close to the true condition. Nothing to note except all the extras. Comes with the original factory box with matching SN, original Target grips, color case hardened target hammer and trigger(installed), color case hardened combat hammer and trigger (looks like they were never used/installed), matching 22 LR cylinder (optional), original spun steel 22 LR inserts (used with the 22 Rem Jet cylinder), original cleaning rod, original paperwork(slightly yellowed due to age), original jacket patch, elaborate SILE target grips in original box and paper (hard to find in this condition!), original Hunter holster - Let's talk about that for a minute; I opened that holster myself when I bought this package. It had never been opened and I personally removed the cellophane (which had yellowed significantly and is still in the box along with the original instruction sheet) and fully expected it to be dry rotted. It wasn't! Looks like new! Also, I know Hunter made "universal" holsters for all brand of firearm. This one is different. On the back of the box, there's only one firearm listed for use with the F-15 holster. You guessed it, the S&W Model 53 with 8 3/8 barrel! What a find this turned out to be. You'll likely never see another collection like this!
 Moving on to the other items. Approximately 750 Hornady 40 grain 22 Jet bullets, complete set of Redding 357 Magnum case reforming dies (Quick Change collars included), original set of RCBS loading dies (Quick Change collars included), Wilson 22 Jet case trimming holder and about 60 cases (some are original 22 Jet head stamped and primed). Everything you need (I'll give light, medium and heavy chronographed load data) to take to the range and enjoy. It's obviously extremely accurate and a lot of fun to shoot. Many will ask what it is as soon as you touch of that first round. It's loud but has very light recoil. You'll find these in varying condition and price. Common 6" models in fair to good condition bring $600+ in todays market. That's usually without the box and extra cylinder. This isn't even in the same class as one of those. That being said, an item is only worth what a seller will take for it and a buyer will pay for it. Mainly interested in high power, long range, big bore rifles. 338 Lapua, 338 RUM, 30 WSM, etc. Would also be interested in high powered handguns. Magnum Research BFR in 45-70, S&W 460 or possible Freedom Arms 454 Casull. Coonan Arms 357 Magnum 1911 or other full size, high quality 1911's in 45 ACP. I'm obviously in no hurry to trade so you may see this one on here for 2 weeks, 2 months or even 2 years! If this listing is up, the firearm is still available. I'll respond quickly to serious offers and/or offers I'm interested in. Low end items or silly responses will not be acknowledged. Would like to stay local but will possibly travel for the right trade. More pictures available. Thanks for your interest!
